<h2>Project Overview</h2>

<div class="section">
<p>
This roadmap outlines the permitting, construction, and inspection process for converting
an existing garage into a legal Accessory Dwelling Unit (ADU) in Portland, Oregon.
</p>
<p>
The project is structured so the <strong>Owner is the permit holder</strong> for administrative
and regulatory items, while <strong>Halli Construction</strong> performs all structural work,
coordination, and interior finish work. The intent of this document is clarity — not
overcomplication.
</p>
</div>

<h2>Roles & Responsibilities</h2>

<div class="section">
<table>
<tr>
<th>Scope</th>
<th>Halli Construction</th>
<th>Owner</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Plans & Technical Documents</td>
<td>✔</td>
<td>—</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Permit Strategy & Coordination</td>
<td>✔</td>
<td>✔</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Structural Construction</td>
<td>✔</td>
<td>—</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Finish Work & Trim</td>
<td>✔</td>
<td>—</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Trade Permits (Owner-Builder)</td>
<td>Coordination</td>
<td>Permit Holder</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Inspection Scheduling</td>
<td>Support</td>
<td>Authorization</td>
</tr>
</table>
</div>

<h2>Phase 1: Administrative Intake</h2>

<div class="section">
<h3>DevHub Account</h3>
<p>
The Owner creates and maintains a profile in the City of Portland’s DevHub system.
All plans, reviews, and approvals are managed through this portal.
</p>
<p>
<a href="https://devhub.portlandoregon.gov/" target="_blank">
https://devhub.portlandoregon.gov/
</a>
</p>
</div>

<div class="section">
<h3>Owner-Builder Acknowledgments</h3>
<p>
Permits are issued under an Owner-Builder structure. Required acknowledgment forms
confirm responsibility for the permit, not the performance of specific tasks.
</p>
<p>
<a href="https://www.portland.gov/ppd/documents/owner-doing-work-form-property-owner-statement-regarding-construction/download" target="_blank">
Owner Doing Work / Owner-Builder Statement (PDF)
</a>
</p>
</div>

<div class="section">
<h3>SDC Waiver</h3>
<p>
System Development Charges (SDCs) for an ADU typically range from
<strong>$12,000–$20,000</strong>. These fees are waived if the Owner agrees not to
use the ADU as a short-term rental for 10 years.
</p>
<p>
<a href="https://www.portland.gov/bds/77447" target="_blank">
SDC Waiver Program Information
</a>
</p>
</div>

<div class="note">
<strong>Critical Requirement:</strong><br>
The SDC Waiver Covenant must be <strong>signed, notarized, and recorded</strong>.
Proof of recording is required before permits can be issued.
</div>

<h2>Phase 2: Construction & Rough-In</h2>

<div class="section">
<h3>Structural Shell</h3>
<p>
Halli Construction completes all structural work, including foundation, framing,
roofing, exterior walls, windows, and weatherproofing.
</p>
</div>

<div class="section">
<h3>Interior Rough-In & Inspections</h3>
<p>
Interior systems are installed and inspected prior to insulation and drywall.
Sequencing and scheduling are coordinated to meet city inspection requirements.
</p>
</div>

<h2>Phase 3: Final Completion & Occupancy</h2>

<div class="section">
<h3>Interior Finish & Trim</h3>
<p>
Halli Construction completes drywall, cabinetry, flooring, trim, fixtures,
and all finish details required for final approval.
</p>
</div>

<div class="section">
<h3>Final Inspection & Certificate of Occupancy</h3>
<p>
Upon final approval, the City issues a Certificate of Occupancy, allowing
the ADU to be legally occupied.
</p>
</div>

<h2>Mandatory Forms & Reference Documents</h2>

<div class="section">
<ul>
<li><a href="https://www.portland.gov/ppd/documents/building-permit-application-building-site-development-demolition-and-zoning-permits/download" target="_blank">
Residential Combination Building Permit Application
</a></li>
<li><a href="https://www.portland.gov/ppd/documents/owner-doing-work-form-property-owner-statement-regarding-construction/download" target="_blank">
Owner Doing Work Statement
</a></li>
<li><a href="https://www.portland.gov/bds/77447" target="_blank">
SDC Waiver & Covenant
</a></li>
<li><a href="https://www.oregon.gov/bcd/codes-stand/Documents/energy-code-residential.pdf" target="_blank">
Oregon Energy Code – Measure A
</a></li>
<li><a href="https://www.portland.gov/ppd/building-and-zoning-permit-application" target="_blank">
Site Plan & Erosion Control Guidance
</a></li>
</ul>
</div>

<h2>Simplified Project Timeline</h2>

<div class="section">
<ol>
<li>DevHub setup & permit preparation — <strong>Owner / Halli Construction</strong></li>
<li>SDC waiver notarization & recording — <strong>Owner</strong></li>
<li>Permit review & issuance — <strong>City of Portland</strong></li>
<li>Structural construction — <strong>Halli Construction</strong></li>
<li>Rough-in inspections — <strong>Coordinated</strong></li>
<li>Interior finish & trim — <strong>Halli Construction</strong></li>
<li>Final inspection & occupancy — <strong>City of Portland</strong></li>
</ol>
</div>

